      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "In a large bowl, evenly season chicken thighs with salt, pepper, paprika, and parsley."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "On high, heat olive oil in a oven-proof pot and place chicken thighs, skin-side down, in the hot oil. Cook 5-6 minutes or the thighs develop brown crispy skin and flip over. Cook an additional 5-6 minutes to brown the other side and remove from the pot."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the garlic and onions to the pot, and cook until the onions are transparent."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Pour in the rice and chicken broth to the pot and season with salt and pepper. Stir well, bringing to a boil."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the chicken thighs back into the pot, skin-side up, on top of the rice, bring back to a boil and cover with a lid."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Bake for 35-40 minutes, or until the rice is fully cooked."
